# Trivy ignore list for CVEs patched at build time via melange.
#
# When a melange pipeline applies a patch (uses: patch) the package version
# string is unchanged, so trivy still matches it against upstream NVD and fires.
# Entries here suppress those false positives explicitly and auditably.
#
# Format: one CVE / GHSA ID per line; inline comments are supported.
# Reference: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore
#
# Each entry MUST have a comment explaining:
#   - which melange patch file applied the fix
#   - when the entry was added so it can be reviewed / expired

# busybox 1.37.0 - patch: melange/CVE-2024-58251.patch - added 2026-04-26
CVE-2024-58251

# busybox 1.37.0 - patch: melange/CVE-2025-46394.patch - added 2026-04-26
CVE-2025-46394

# busybox 1.37.0 - patch: melange/CVE-2025-60876.patch - added 2026-04-26
CVE-2025-60876
